 snowboard barely make a track. You could trigger a small pocket that could take you for a nasty ride. Start and end your day early to avoid small wet avalanches in the afternoon.<\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"a9d631e6-e571-4eda-8680-ee513dc49e83","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776627971\/AvIDfx\/x4y83rj9qjutcftkmg3n.webp","width":1194,"height":1994,"credit":"","caption":"<p>It's LOW (1 of 5) danger across the state, and conditions are generally safe on most slopes. Still, as backcountry travelers step into bigger and more consequential terrain, you might be able to find stiff areas of drifted snow where you could trigger a small avalanche. These avalanches could be dangerous if you get knocked off your feet and tumble down the slope, especially in consequential terrain.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A small avalanche in steep terrain.","dateTaken":"2026-04-15T17:54:44Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"cbfcfedd-e5fd-4b60-9f85-ef12f77086ce","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776712322\/AvIDfx\/dsia0zlksm5gf3ujqraj.webp","width":2500,"height":3333,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Sunny, warm weather this time of year means there's potential for small, loose activity on steep, sunny slopes in the afternoon. Head for the shade or less-steep slopes if you find yourself sinking above your ankles into wet, mushy snow.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A ski track near a small loose avalanche below rocks","dateTaken":"2026-04-19T18:44:54Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"5d4c8e31-4b1f-4c0f-a6d2-1d112c5382ba","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776626442\/AvIDfx\/ewjernxtatf09wyqbbd3.webp","width":1536,"height":2048,"credit":"","caption":"<p>A small avalanche triggered in the wrong place can quickly turn a good day into a bad one. Luckily for this rider, they avoided getting carried into the rocks. This Wind Slab avalanche was triggered near Guanella Pass on Saturday. This avalanche was small, but it did manage to knock a backcountry traveller off their feet, and it was triggered in an area of firm, wind-drifted snow near the top of the slope. Assess the reactivity of these stiffened slabs by looking for cracking in drifted features. It's also a good idea to look below to assess the consequences of taking a small ride before committing to a steep slope.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A skier looking up at a freshly triggered avalanche in a gully. ","dateTaken":"2026-04-18T19:35:17.706Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"a9d45854-eb92-445a-9880-23c5feb3932e","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776456658\/AvIDfx\/sjqt6cb2byg2a8kslif0.webp","width":2500,"height":3333,"credit":"","caption":"<p>If riding in steeper terrain, manage your sluff so you don't get knocked down or swept into consequential terrain features. Any avalanche will likely be small, but even a small avalanche can quickly turn a good day into a bad one if triggered in extreme terrain. <\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Small sluff in steep gulley","dateTaken":"2026-04-16T19:51:59.173Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-22T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-23T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-24T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[],[],[]]}},{"id":"b10966ce-facb-426f-b365-eced34082321","publicName":"1-100-101-103-109-111-114-115-146-147-15-16-22-23-27-28-47-57-58-68-7-8","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["0BFCE84E-A2A4-4986-BF7D-84C1A0A2E467","0EF68DA6-9B2C-4366-BF30-4256AE6340BA","20D852D8-E47A-4447-ABE2-05E5F5E022D0","21F30165-D180-48B5-A36F-830F4DA1E8ED","30232C29-4A0C-4D7A-B951-EF7B873C2CBF","46C849AB-16F5-441C-9320-D501C858D14A","59C37E11-7808-47BD-9C61-8D4F6F7F2A04","72121255-B904-4013-887A-6A179A9C